item.title: How do i?
item.dc:creator: @BobDole81 BobDole81
item.description:
@BobDole81 wrote:

RAR passwords are quite difficult to crack as the hash algorithm used apparently takes quite some time perform. There are, of course, RAR password crackers, but all they will do is brute force and perform dictionary attacks. My best brute forcing speed for rar archives is about 25 pw/s compared to the 12 million pw/s I can do for zip archives.

Its pretty hopeless trying to retrieve rar passwords imo (using the software I’ve seen at least).
